<item>
            <title>[SEC-3031] DelegatingSecurityContextRunnable &amp; DelegatingSecurityContextCallable should only modify SecurityContext when invoked on new Thread</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-3031</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When an ExecutorService (ThreadPoolExecutor) is setup with a CallerRunsPolicy for the RejectedExecutionHandler and the caller thread is used to run the task, the spring security DelegatingSecurityContextCallable and DelegatingSecurityContextRunnable blindly clear the security context upon completion - effectively clearing the security context for the calling thread.  In this case, it should not clear the context.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="64631">SEC-3031</key>
            <summary>DelegatingSecurityContextRunnable &amp; DelegatingSecurityContextCallable should only modify SecurityContext when invoked on new Thread</summary>
